hpnicfdot1sMstp.name: hpnicfdot1sMstp

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB file.

hpnicfdot1sMstp.description: This MIB defines objects for managing MSTP.

EnabledStatus.name: EnabledStatus
EnabledStatus.description: A simple status value for the object.

Hpnicfdot1sFormatStatus.name: Hpnicfdot1sFormatStatus
Hpnicfdot1sFormatStatus.description: Legacy means that the BPDU format is legacy. Dot1s means that the BPDU format is IEEE 802.1s. Auto means that the format of BPDU sending on the port is determined by the BPDU format of its connective port.

hpnicfdot1sStpStatus.name: hpnicfdot1sStpStatus
hpnicfdot1sStpStatus.description: Whether the Bridge MSTP is enabled.

hpnicfdot1sStpForceVersion.name: hpnicfdot1sStpForceVersion
hpnicfdot1sStpForceVersion.description: The mode of this Bridge spanning-tree protocol.

hpnicfdot1sMstBridgeMaxHops.name: hpnicfdot1sMstBridgeMaxHops
hpnicfdot1sMstBridgeMaxHops.description: The maximum value of the Bridge hops.

hpnicfdot1sMstMasterBridgeID.name: hpnicfdot1sMstMasterBridgeID
hpnicfdot1sMstMasterBridgeID.description: The Bridge Identifier of the current Master Bridge.

hpnicfdot1sMstMasterPathCost.name: hpnicfdot1sMstMasterPathCost
hpnicfdot1sMstMasterPathCost.description: The CIST path cost from the transmitting Bridge to the Master Bridge.

hpnicfdot1sMstBpduGuard.name: hpnicfdot1sMstBpduGuard
hpnicfdot1sMstBpduGuard.description: Whether the Bridge BPDU Guard function is enabled. If the function is enabled, the port will shutdown when received BPDU and the port is configured as portfast.

hpnicfdot1sMstAdminFormatSelector.name: hpnicfdot1sMstAdminFormatSelector
hpnicfdot1sMstAdminFormatSelector.description: The administrative Configuration Identifier Format Selector in use by the Bridge. This has a value of 0 indicate the format specified in the Standard of IEEE 802.1s.

hpnicfdot1sMstOperFormatSelector.name: hpnicfdot1sMstOperFormatSelector
hpnicfdot1sMstOperFormatSelector.description: The operative Configuration Identifier Format Selector in use by the Bridge. This has a value of 0 indicate the format specified in the Standard of IEEE 802.1s.

hpnicfdot1sMstOperConfigDigest.name: hpnicfdot1sMstOperConfigDigest
hpnicfdot1sMstOperConfigDigest.description: This MSTP Region's Configuration Digest Signature Key.

hpnicfdot1sMstDefaultVlanAllo.name: hpnicfdot1sMstDefaultVlanAllo
hpnicfdot1sMstDefaultVlanAllo.description: Set default configuration about VLAN allocation and all VLANs are mapped to CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiBridgeID.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiBridgeID
hpnicfdot1sMstiBridgeID.description: The Bridge Identifier for the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hpnicfdot1sMstiBridgePriority.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiBridgePriority
hpnicfdot1sMstiBridgePriority.description: The Bridge Priority for the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID. Step of 4096

hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignedRoot.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignedRoot
hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignedRoot.description: The Bridge Identifier of the Root Bridge for the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hpnicfdot1sMstiRootPathCost.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiRootPathCost
hpnicfdot1sMstiRootPathCost.description: The path cost from the transmitting Bridge to the Root Bridge for the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hpnicfdot1sMstiRootPort.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiRootPort
hpnicfdot1sMstiRootPort.description: The Root Port for the spanning tree instance identified by the MSTID

hpnicfdot1sMstiRootType.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiRootType
hpnicfdot1sMstiRootType.description: Config this Bridge as a primary root or secondary root and or cancel the root for this spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hpnicfdot1sMstiRemainingHops.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiRemainingHops
hpnicfdot1sMstiRemainingHops.description: The remaining hops of the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hpnicfdot1sMstiAdminMappedVlanListLow.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiAdminMappedVlanListLow
hpnicfdot1sMstiAdminMappedVlanListLow.description: The lower part of administrative Vlan list mapped to the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hpnicfdot1sMstiAdminMappedVlanListHigh.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiAdminMappedVlanListHigh
hpnicfdot1sMstiAdminMappedVlanListHigh.description: The higher part of administrative Vlan list mapped to the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hpnicfdot1sMstiOperMappedVlanListLow.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiOperMappedVlanListLow
hpnicfdot1sMstiOperMappedVlanListLow.description: The lower part of operative Vlan list mapped to the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hpnicfdot1sMstiOperMappedVlanListHigh.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiOperMappedVlanListHigh
hpnicfdot1sMstiOperMappedVlanListHigh.description: The higher part of operative Vlan list mapped to the spanning tree instance identified by MSTID

hpnicfdot1sMstiPortIndex.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiPortIndex
hpnicfdot1sMstiPortIndex.description: The index of the Bridge Port

hpnicfdot1sMstiState.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiState
hpnicfdot1sMstiState.description: The current state of the Port (i.e., Disabled, Discarding , Learning, Forwarding)

hpnicfdot1sMstiPortPriority.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiPortPriority
hpnicfdot1sMstiPortPriority.description: The value of the priority field which is contained in the first (in network byte order) four bits of the (2 octet long) Port ID. The other octet of the Port ID is given by the value of mstiPortIndex. And step of 16

hpnicfdot1sMstiPathCost.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiPathCost
hpnicfdot1sMstiPathCost.description: The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the spanning tree root which include this port. The range of path cost is 1..65535 for 802.1d standard, is 1..200000000 for 802.1t standard, and is 1..200000 for the legacy standard.

hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignatedRoot.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignatedRoot
hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignatedRoot.description: The Bridge Identifier of the Root Bridge for the port of the Spanning Tree instance identified by the MSTID

hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignatedCost.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignatedCost
hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the Designated Port of the segment connected to this port. This value is compared to the Root Path Cost field in received bridge PDUs.

hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignatedBridge.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignatedBridge
hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignatedBridge.description: The Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignatedPort.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignatedPort
hpnicfdot1sMstiDesignatedPort.description: The Port Identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

hpnicfdot1sMstiMasterBridgeID.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiMasterBridgeID
hpnicfdot1sMstiMasterBridgeID.description: The Bridge Identifier of the current Master Bridge. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiMasterPortCost.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiMasterPortCost
hpnicfdot1sMstiMasterPortCost.description: The CIST path cost from the transmitting Bridge to the Master Bridge. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortEdgeport.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortEdgeport
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortEdgeport.description: Whether the port fast is enabled. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint.description: Whether the port connects the point to point link. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpMcheck.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpMcheck
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpMcheck.description: Forcing the state machine to send MST BPDUs in this manner can be used to test whether all legacy Bridges on a given LAN have been removed. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTransLimit.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTransLimit
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTransLimit.description: The value used by the Port Transmit state machine to limit the maximum transmission rate. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpRXStpBPDU.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpRXStpBPDU
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpRXStpBPDU.description: The number of received Config BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTXStpBPDU.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTXStpBPDU
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTXStpBPDU.description: The number of transmitted Config BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpRXTCNBPDU.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpRXTCNBPDU
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpRXTCNBPDU.description: The number of received TCN BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTXTCNBPDU.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTXTCNBPDU
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTXTCNBPDU.description: The number of transmitted TCN BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpRXRSTPBPDU.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpRXRSTPBPDU
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpRXRSTPBPDU.description: The number of received RST BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTXRSTPBPDU.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTXRSTPBPDU
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTXRSTPBPDU.description: The number of transmitted RST BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpRXMSTPBPDU.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpRXMSTPBPDU
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpRXMSTPBPDU.description: The number of received MST BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTXMSTPBPDU.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTXMSTPBPDU
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpTXMSTPBPDU.description: The number of transmitted MST BPDU. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpClearStatistics.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpClearStatistics
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpClearStatistics.description: Clear the spanning tree statistic. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpStatus.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpStatus
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpStatus.description: Whether the spanning tree protocol is enabled on this port. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiPortRootGuard.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiPortRootGuard
hpnicfdot1sMstiPortRootGuard.description: Whether the root guard is enabled. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiPortLoopGuard.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiPortLoopGuard
hpnicfdot1sMstiPortLoopGuard.description: Whether the loop protection is enabled. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortSendingBPDUType.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortSendingBPDUType
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortSendingBPDUType.description: Type of BPDU which the port is sending.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpOperPortPointToPoint.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpOperPortPointToPoint
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpOperPortPointToPoint.description: This object indicates whether the port has connected to a point-to-point link or not. The value of the node is an operative value. The administrative value can be read from the node hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint. If the value of hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint is auto, the value of this node should be calculated by the network topology of this port. If the value of hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint is forceFalse, the value of this node is false. If the value of hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortPointToPoint is forceTrue, the value of this node is true.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortAdminBPDUFmt.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortAdminBPDUFmt
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortAdminBPDUFmt.description: The value of the node is an administrative value. Value legacy means that the MST BPDU format is forced to legacy. Value dot1s means that the MST BPDU format is forced to IEEE 802.1s. Value auto means that the format of MST BPDU sending on the port is determined by the MST BPDU that the port has received. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortOperBPDUFmt.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortOperBPDUFmt
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortOperBPDUFmt.description: The format of MST BPDU which the port is sending. Value legacy means that the format of MST BPDU sending on the port is legacy. Value dot1s means that the format of MST BPDU sending on the port is IEEE 802.1s. Effective in CIST.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortRoleRestriction.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortRoleRestriction
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortRoleRestriction.description: Whether the role-restriction is enabled. Effective in CIST. The role-restriction causes the port not to be selected as root port for the CIST or any MSTI.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortTcRestriction.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortTcRestriction
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortTcRestriction.description: Whether the tc-restriction is enabled. Effective in CIST. The tc-restriction causes the port not to propagate topology changes to other ports.

hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortDisputed.name: hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortDisputed
hpnicfdot1sMstiStpPortDisputed.description: Whether the port is disputed for the CIST or MSTI.

hpnicfdot1sStpPathCostStandard.name: hpnicfdot1sStpPathCostStandard
hpnicfdot1sStpPathCostStandard.description: Path cost standard of the bridge. Value dot1d-1998 is IEEE 802.1d standard in 1998, value dot1t is IEEE 802.1t standard, and value legacy is a private legacy standard.

hpnicfPortMstiStateForwarding.name: hpnicfPortMstiStateForwarding
hpnicfPortMstiStateForwarding.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a port turns into forwarding state form other state.

hpnicfPortMstiStateDiscarding.name: hpnicfPortMstiStateDiscarding
hpnicfPortMstiStateDiscarding.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a port turns into discarding state form forwarding state.

hpnicfBridgeLostRootPrimary.name: hpnicfBridgeLostRootPrimary
hpnicfBridgeLostRootPrimary.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when the bridge is no longer the root bridge of the instance. Another switch with higher priority has already been the root bridge of the instance.

hpnicfPortMstiRootGuarded.name: hpnicfPortMstiRootGuarded
hpnicfPortMstiRootGuarded.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when a root-guard port receives a superior message on the relevant instance.

hpnicfPortMstiBpduGuarded.name: hpnicfPortMstiBpduGuarded
hpnicfPortMstiBpduGuarded.description: The SNMP trap is generated when an edged port of the BPDU-guard device receives a BPDU. If the designated bridge ID can't be obtained from the BPDU, the designated bridge ID will be zero.

hpnicfPortMstiLoopGuarded.name: hpnicfPortMstiLoopGuarded
hpnicfPortMstiLoopGuarded.description: The SNMP trap that is generated when an Alternate-Port or Root-Port is aged out.

hpnicfMstiNewRoot.name: hpnicfMstiNewRoot
hpnicfMstiNewRoot.description: The SNMP trap is generated when the sending device becomes the new root of the spanning tree. The first root bridge ID means the old root bridge ID, and the second one means the new root bridge ID.

hpnicfPortPvstBpduProtection.name: hpnicfPortPvstBpduProtection
hpnicfPortPvstBpduProtection.description: The SNMP trap is generated when a PVST BPDU is received on an MSTP port that is enabled with the PVST protection feature. If the designated bridge ID can't be obtained from the BPDU, the designated bridge ID will be zero.
